{{see|crusade}}
==English==

===Etymology===
[[Image:Gustave dore crusades entry of the crusaders into constantinople.jpg|right|thumb|Crusaders]]
From the French ''[[croisade]]'', meaning “Marked by the Cross.” It is derived from the Latin word ''[[crux]]'' (cross).

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|s}}

# One of a series of ostensibly [[religious]] [[campaign]]s by [[Christian]] forces from the 11th to the 13th century, mostly to capture the [[Holy Land]] from the [[Muslim]]s who occupied it.

{{wikipedia}}

